      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Wall shear stress distribution validation via PIV measurements",
      "description": "Particle image velocimetry (PIV) data from FDA benchmark study used to validate near-wall velocity gradients and derived shear stress distributions in the volute region. Spatial correlation coefficient R=0.91 between CFD and PIV velocity fields. This result directly supports the hemolysis power-law model which is shear-stress driven. Note: uncertainty quantification for this validation result was deferred pending completion of the expanded PIV dataset acquisition; interim assessment proceeds on deterministic comparison only.",
      "validationScope": "Near-wall shear stress in volute and impeller-outlet region",
      "comparisonMetric": "Spatial correlation coefficient and point-wise relative error at 47 PIV measurement locations"
